      "span_text": "Neadal demonstrated that because of low systemic concentrations, topical NSAIDs have a reduced risk of upper gastrointestinal complications, such as gastric and peptic ulcers, and gastrointestinal nuisance symptoms, such as dyspepsia. Parenteral drug delivery with intravenous, subcutaneous, or intramuscular injection, can gain easy access to systemic circulation with rapid drug absorption."
